{"parse":{"title":"Project Hindsight","pageid":39181419,"revid":852247655,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Project Hindsight</b> was a <a href=\"/wiki/Retrospective\" title=\"Retrospective\">retrospective</a> study conducted to determine the effectiveness of several <a href=\"/wiki/Aftermath_of_World_War_II\" title=\"Aftermath of World War II\">post-World War II</a> weapons research projects.<sup id=\"cite_ref-highbeam1_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-highbeam1-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  The project was conducted by the Office of the Director of Defense Research and Engineering, a sub-agency of the <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Department_of_Defense\" title=\"United States Department of Defense\">United States Department of Defense</a>.  \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Project_parameters\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Project parameters</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Project_findings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Project findings</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Responses_to_Project_Hindsight\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Responses to Project Hindsight</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Further_reading\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Further reading</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Project_parameters\">Project parameters</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Project_Hindsight&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Project parameters\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The study ran from 1963 to 1967<sup id=\"cite_ref-jstor1_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-jstor1-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and the final report was published in October 1969 and released to the public in September 1970.<sup id=\"cite_ref-dtic1_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-dtic1-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>  The project had two goals: the first was to identify R&amp;D management productivity and the second was to measure the overall <a href=\"/wiki/Cost-effectiveness_analysis\" title=\"Cost-effectiveness analysis\">cost-effectiveness</a> of using recently developed weapon systems compared to their predecessors that were in use 10 to 20 years earlier.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Sherwin_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Sherwin-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Project_findings\">Project findings</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Project_Hindsight&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Project findings\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Of all 'events' studied by Project Hindsight, 91% were technological, and only 9% were classed as science. Within the latter category 8.7% were applied science, whereas only 0.3%, or two 'events', were due to basic or undirected science.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Sherwin_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Sherwin-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Responses_to_Project_Hindsight\">Responses to Project Hindsight</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Project_Hindsight&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Responses to Project Hindsight\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>As <a href=\"/wiki/Science_and_technology_studies\" title=\"Science and technology studies\">science and technology studies</a> scholar Edwin Layton observed in 1971, 'the publication of these results produced a spate of indignant letters to the editors of <i>Science</i>.' He noted that many of these letters missed the point, and instead should focus on the interaction between science and technology rather than attempting to demonstrate that fundamental scientific research influences technology development more than Project Hindsight had suggested.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>He also called attention to a subsequent study, <i>Technology in Retrospect and Critical Events in Science</i> (TRACES), which 'revealed cases in which mission-oriented research or development effort elicited later nonmission research, which often was found to be crucial to the ultimate innovation'.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Project_Hindsight&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-highbeam1-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-highbeam1_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Kostoff, Ronald N. (1 January 1993). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-13832964.html\">\"Research impact assessment\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Business_Economics_(journal)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Business Economics (journal)\">Business Economics</a></i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">17 March</span> 2013</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Business+Economics&amp;rft.atitle=Research+impact+assessment&amp;rft.date=1993-01-01&amp;rft.aulast=Kostoff&amp;rft.aufirst=Ronald+N.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.highbeam.com%2Fdoc%2F1G1-13832964.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AProject+Hindsight\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-jstor1-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-jstor1_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Kreilkamp, Karl (January 1971). \"Hindsight and the Real World of Science Policy\". <i>Science Studies</i>. <b>1</b> (1): 43\u201366. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1177/030631277100100104\">10.1177/030631277100100104</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/JSTOR\" title=\"JSTOR\">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.jstor.org/stable/370196\">370196</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Science+Studies&amp;rft.atitle=Hindsight+and+the+Real+World+of+Science+Policy&amp;rft.volume=1&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=43-66&amp;rft.date=1971-01&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1177%2F030631277100100104&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F370196&amp;rft.au=Kreilkamp%2C+Karl&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AProject+Hindsight\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-dtic1-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-dtic1_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://oai.dtic.mil/oai/oai?verb=getRecord&amp;metadataPrefix=html&amp;identifier=AD0495905\">\"Project HINDSIGHT - Summary\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Defense_Technical_Information_Center\" title=\"Defense Technical Information Center\">Defense Technical Information Center</a>. October 1969<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">17 March </span> 2013</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Project+HINDSIGHT+-+Summary&amp;rft.pub=Defense+Technical+Information+Center&amp;rft.date=1969-10&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Foai.dtic.mil%2Foai%2Foai%3Fverb%3DgetRecord%26metadataPrefix%3Dhtml%26identifier%3DAD0495905&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AProject+Hindsight\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Sherwin-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Sherwin_4-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Sherwin_4-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Sherwin CW, Isenson RS (23 June 1967). \"Project hindsight. A Defense Department study of the utility of research\". <i>Science</i>. <b>156</b>: 1571\u20137. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1126/science.156.3782.1571\">10.1126/science.156.3782.1571</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/PubMed_Identifier\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"PubMed Identifier\">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/6025113\">6025113</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Science&amp;rft.atitle=Project+hindsight.+A+Defense+Department+study+of+the+utility+of+research.&amp;rft.volume=156&amp;rft.pages=1571-7&amp;rft.date=1967-06-23&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.156.3782.1571&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F6025113&amp;rft.au=Sherwin+CW%2C+Isenson+RS&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AProject+Hindsight\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">D. S. Greenberg, 'Hindsight: DOD Study Examines Return on Investment in Research' <i>Science</i> 154 (November 18, 1966): 872-73</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Philip H. Abelson, 'Project Hindsight,' <i>Science</i> 154 (December 2, 1966): 1123.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Edwin Layton, 'Mirror-Image Twins: The Communities of Science and Technology in 19th-Century America', <i>Technology and Culture</i>, Vol. 12, No. 4 (Oct., 1971), pp. 562-580</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Illinois Institute of Technology Research Institute, <i>Technology in Retrospect and Critical Events in Science</i>, 2 vols. (n. p. [Chicago], 1968).</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Further_reading\">Further reading</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><